---
// Collapsible methodology — transparent about data sources and estimation
---

<div class="glass mb-4">
  <button id="methodToggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-4 text-left">
    <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-white">Methodology &amp; Data Sources</span>
    <svg id="methodArrow" class="collapse-arrow w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
    </svg>
  </button>
  <div id="methodContent" class="hidden px-4 pb-4 text-xs text-neutral-400 space-y-2">
    <p><strong class="text-neutral-300">Data sources:</strong>
    <strong class="text-neutral-300">LinkedIn</strong>, <strong class="text-neutral-300">Indeed</strong>,
    <strong class="text-neutral-300">Google Jobs</strong> (via JobSpy),
    <strong class="text-neutral-300">JobsDB</strong> (GraphQL API),
    <strong class="text-neutral-300">Lever</strong> and <strong class="text-neutral-300">Greenhouse</strong> (ATS APIs for major tech/finance companies).
    Refreshed daily via GitHub Actions. All data is publicly available job postings.</p>

    <p><strong class="text-neutral-300">Salary estimation:</strong>
    Singapore salaries are estimated using industry benchmarks from
    <a href="https://sg.jobsdb.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-400">JobsDB Singapore</a>,
    <a href="https://www.payscale.com/research/SG/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-400">PayScale Singapore 2026</a>, and
    <a href="https://www.roberthalf.com/sg/en/insights/salary-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-400">Robert Half Singapore Salary Guide 2026</a>.
    The model uses 5 signals: seniority level, company tier, role category, Employment Pass eligibility, and premium skill keywords.
    Confidence is rated High (3+ signals), Medium (1–2), or Low (baseline only).
    Rajesh's minimum salary expectation: <strong>SGD 13,000/month</strong> (currently earning SGD 15,000).</p>

    <p><strong class="text-neutral-300">Fit score:</strong> Measures how well a job title matches the selected category (e.g., selecting "Fraud Investigator" ranks fraud/financial crime investigator titles higher).</p>

    <p><strong class="text-neutral-300">Match score:</strong> Measures alignment with Rajesh's skill profile: SQL, Power BI, Tableau, Python, Microsoft Azure, Scikit-Learn, XGBoost, and emerging tools (OpenAI APIs, Prompt Engineering). Title keywords contribute up to 30 points, description skills up to 70.</p>

    <p><strong class="text-neutral-300">Employment Pass Friendly:</strong> Flags ~50 known international companies (banks, Big4, FAANG, etc.) plus jobs mentioning visa sponsorship, work permits, relocation support, or diverse/global teams.</p>

    <p><strong class="text-neutral-300">Deduplication:</strong> 3-layer system &mdash; URL canonicalization, exact title+company matching, and fuzzy matching (70%+ title similarity) across all sources. Prevents the same job from appearing twice.</p>

    <p><strong class="text-neutral-300">Tech stack:</strong> Python (async httpx, Pydantic, pandas), Astro.js + Tailwind CSS frontend, Chart.js visualizations, 134 unit tests (pytest), GitHub Actions CI/CD, Vercel/Hostinger deployment.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<script is:inline>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
  var t = document.getElementById('methodToggle');
  if (t) t.addEventListener('click', function() {
    document.getElementById('methodContent').classList.toggle('hidden');
    document.getElementById('methodArrow').classList.toggle('open');
  });
});
</script>
